The paper deals with algorithms for finding the global sink in a unique sink orientation of a grid, which is a problem in discrete mathematics and theoretical computer science. The paper uses techniques from computational geometry and graph theory, which are common in the sub-categories of cs.DS (data structures and algorithms), cs.CC (computational complexity), and cs.CG (computational geometry). The paper also involves combinatorial optimization, which is a topic in cs.DM (discrete mathematics). Finally, the paper mentions the concept of game theory, which is a sub-topic of cs.GT (game theory).
